CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 20, 1962, page 7, reads: "Enlightening Youths - On Baxter's program were, left to right: Dr. Earl Childs, the Rev. Arthanniel Harris, Mrs. Shirley Biggs, Patrolman Harold Moten, school nurse Jean Hagaman, Atty. Linn B. Washington and Dr. James Stewart. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two women and five men, including left to right: Dr. Earl Childs, Reverend Arthanniel Harris, Shirley Biggs, Police Officer Harold Moten, nurse Jean Hagaman, attorney Linn B. Washington, and Dr. James Stewart, seated behind table on stage at Baxter School with light colored curtain and posters that read "Workers in Pittsburgh" and "The Mayor of Pittsburgh Our mayor is Joseph Barr. His job is to see that all the city workers..."
